definitions.definition: Any of several species of tufted grasses of the genus Lolium .
examples: Perennial ryegrass is an important species for lawn seed mixes.

definitions.definition: A collection of plants of any of the species, as in a lawn or field .
examples: We seeded the meadow with ryegrass to provide better forage.

main_definition: ( countable ) Any of several species of tufted grasses of the genus Lolium .
secondary_definitions: ( uncountable ) A collection of plants of any of the species, as in a lawn or field .
